      Get valuable responsibility early
   =20
 =20
This  article about Matthew Grimes, a 27-year-old Wharton graduate who=C2=
=A0works for Tom Barrack and was arrested with him on charges of acting as =
unregistered foreign agents for the United Arab Emirates, is not really cor=
e Money Stuff subject matter, but I do want to spend a minute enjoying the =
headline, which is =E2=80=9CFrom Intern to Co-Defendant.=E2=80=9D That is r=
eally the dream career path. You start out as an intern just making copies =
and getting coffee =E2=80=94=C2=A0=E2=80=9Caboard Barrack=E2=80=99s private=
 planes, Grimes would graciously serve tea and crackers, and was sometimes =
called upon to book restaurant reservations=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94=C2=A0but if =
you work hard and are a good team player you will rapidly progress. You=E2=
=80=99ll get face time with the boss, take on increasing responsibility, be=
 put in front of clients, lead your own deals =E2=80=94=C2=A0Grimes =E2=80=
=9Cwas also president of a related special purpose acquisition vehicle=E2=
=80=9D =E2=80=94=C2=A0and, if everything works out just right, you=E2=80=99=
ll end up charged in the same federal criminal prosecution as the boss. Tha=
t=E2=80=99s how you know you=E2=80=99ve made it.
